*      here is a global tuning for BE32 on udsc quarks at the Z        
*-------------------------------------------------------------------
*  here is a global tuning including BE_32c model by G.Rudolph 
*  December 2001 fot Pythia 6.1 3rd iteration
*-------------------------------------------------------------------
MSTG  11  /  3    ! mixed scheme in frag
MSTG  12  /  2    !  old diquark + popcorn ( ie =3 in JETSET 7.4)
MSTG  46  /  3    ! azimuthal isotropy in PS ( def)
*   parton shower parameters :
PARG 81 / 0.286   ! LAMBDA QCD was .291 in Jetset 7.4
PARG 82 / 1.73   ! M min.     was 1.52
*   flavor-neutral fragmentation parameters  :
PARG 21 / 0.379   ! SIGMA MT   was .371
PARG 41 / 0.505   ! a          was .4
PARG 42 / 0.800   ! B          was .805
PARG 54 / -0.040 ! Epsilon_c  
PARG 55 / -0.0020 ! Epsilon_b  was -0.0035
*   following is standard ....
PARG   1  / 0.108  ! qq/q
PARG   2  / 0.286  ! s/u
PARG   3  / 0.690  ! su/du
PARG  11  / 0.553  ! V_ud
PARG  12  / 0.470  ! V_s
PARG  13  / 0.65   ! V_cb
PARG  14  / 0.120  ! = PARJ(16) P(1+)
PARG  15  / 0.040  ! = PARJ(17)/5.  P(0+)
PARG  16  / 0.120  ! = 3.*PARJ(17)/5.  P(1+)
PARG  17  / 0.20   ! PARJ(14-17) give higher meson nonets (tensor... P(2+)
PARG  19  / 0.55   ! leading baryon suppre 
PARG  26  / 0.276  ! eta-prime suppress.
*    special for BE_32
MSTG 51  / 2   !   BE on Gaussian
MSTG 52  / 9   !   part. involved 
MSTG 53  / 1   ! all pions, 1 = only pions from same W, 2 = only fron diff.Ws
MSTG 54  / 2   !   BE_32 model
PARG 92  / 1.14   !  /\_BE
PARG 93  / 0.342   ! sigma_BE
*-----------------------end-global tuning-------------------------------



